<div class="artwrap">
  <article class="article reveal">
    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>CNO Pole Barns has been putting up post-frame buildings in southeast Michigan since 1970. Today the company runs three full-time crews out of Clarkston, building garages, barns, barndominiums, and pre-engineered steel buildings across Oakland, Genesee, Lapeer, and Macomb counties.</p>
    <p>The company is locally owned, licensed and insured, and carries an A+ rating with the Better Business Bureau. Owner Zosim Serban quotes every job himself.</p>

    <figure class="inline-img riv">
      <img src="/images/team/cno-crew.jpg" alt="Five CNO crew members on a job site with barn posts set behind them" width="1152" height="810" loading="lazy">
      <figcaption>Part of the CNO crew on post-setting day.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>How we work</h2>
    <p>Reviews on Google keep mentioning the same things: the phone gets answered, the schedule holds up, and the crew doesn't leave a mess behind. You deal with the same people from the estimate to the final walkthrough, and the contract numbers don't move once the work starts.</p>

    <figure class="inline-img riv">
      <img src="/images/team/zosim-serban-2.jpg" alt="Portrait of Zosim Serban, owner of CNO Pole Barns" width="1424" height="1440" loading="lazy">
      <figcaption>Zosim Serban, owner of CNO Pole Barns.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <blockquote>
      <p>"Zosim was on top of the project from start to finish and always available to review any questions that came up... After foundation and blocks were in place, the general structure was up in one day, the roof shingled the next morning... There were no surprises concerning financials."</p>
      <p>- Reimund B., 24'x30' garage, Google review</p>
    </blockquote>

    <blockquote>
      <p>"We had some issues being in the city with permits but Zosim was always on top of any problem that arose. Communication was phenomenal. I highly recommend this company."</p>
      <p>- Heather B., garage rebuild after a fire, Google review</p>
    </blockquote>

    <p>The crews clean up when a job's done, too. It's a small thing that shows up in almost every review we get.</p>

